g one. During the Clone Wars they were considered antiquities, and collectors paid many credits for these vessels. The vessel rotated while in flight, which was its main source of propulsion. As such, they also gave off a distinct humming sound while in flight. They had enough room for 6 Flarestar-class Weequay ships, which could be launched from the center of its ventral superstructure. The craft was capable of landing on planetary surfaces and had eight landing legs. The eighth doubled as boarding ramps. The pirate band of Hondo Ohnaka used such a ship to carry out their raids. Ohnaka stole the ship from a starship collector on Farana along with several Flarestar-class Weequay ships. They landed on Vanqor during Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker''s hunt for Count Dooku, and scavenged the Count''s Punworcca 116-class interstellar sloop. Ohnaka offered the Count passage to Florrum, a planet six parsecs away. Dooku accepted the offer to travel with them in the ship to their base on Florrum.','Corona Armed Frigate.png',NULL,'Source text CC-BY-SA 3.0 from http://d6holocron.com/wiki/Corona%20Armed%20Frigate','["http://d6holocron.com/wiki/Corona%20Armed%20Frigate"]',13277,27089);
